 Bigboy Sibande, Thulani Dumisa and Tanderayi Sithole were arrested after police received information of a video on social media where Bigboy Sibande was captured in possession of a firearm. After following up on the lead, the police was led to Sibande’s house where they recovered the firearm and Sibande’s brother and his girlfriend were taken in for questioning. Upon hearing the news, Sibande went to the police station to hand himself over. A further probe into the matter revealed that Sibande and his accomplices had allegedly broken into a house on a farm in the Loskop area on 15 March 2018. They reportedly stole the firearm, a home theatre system, other technology, shoes and bags, which have all been recovered.
It futher transpired that Tanderayi was an employee on the farm. The suspects were remanded in custody and the case was postponed to 25 March, 2019, for bail application.     Parents frustrated by a lack of space in Middelburg schools Traffic officers to appear in court for corruption #TrafficAlert: Two dead in Kranspoort accidents VIDEO: Two perish after truck jack-knifes • Save our standby number (072 248 3855) and send us a WhatsApp message with the words “Add me” to be added to our broadcast list. • Like us on Facebook, follow us on Twitter and Instagram. • Subscribe to our YouTube channel. • Click on the link to subscribe to our bi-weekly newsletter via email. Contact our news room on our 24 hr standby number 072 248 3855, or send a mail to our editor tobie@mobserver.co.za